codex
The core engine tests pass, but the new observable F9 explain fields are not propagated through the public Python and TypeScript SDK wrappers. Public SDK callers will not see the contribution this patch intends to expose.

Full review comments:

- [P2] Propagate explain weights through the Python wrapper — /home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb-worktrees/0.8.16-slice-5-20260708T114929Z/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-py/src/lib.rs:545-546
  Adding `importance`/`confidence` to the native `PyPerHitExplain` object does not make them visible to normal Python SDK callers: `src/python/fathomdb/engine.py` still rebuilds `fathomdb.types.PerHitExplain` without these fields, and `types.py`/`_fathomdb.pyi` do not declare them. In the scenario covered by this change (`Engine.search(..., explain=True)` with F9 enabled), the native values are silently dropped before the public result is returned.

- [P2] Propagate explain weights through the TypeScript wrapper — /home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb-worktrees/0.8.16-slice-5-20260708T114929Z/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-napi/src/lib.rs:616-617
  The native N-API object now includes `importance` and `confidence`, but the TypeScript SDK still omits them from `NativePerHitExplain`, the public `PerHitExplain` interface, and the `perHit` mapping in `src/ts/src/index.ts`. For `search(..., { explain: true })` callers, the F9 contribution is therefore discarded even though the Rust binding produced it.
